.TH syscalls 2 2026-07-10 "VibeOS System Calls"
.SH NAME
syscalls \- system calls recognized by VibeOS
.SH DESCRIPTION
VibeOS implements an ABI-compatible subset of the Linux x86-64 syscall ABI.
Numbers not listed below return
.BR ENOSYS .
The presence of a call does not imply complete Linux semantics.
.SS Files, paths, and descriptors
.TP
.B 0-8
read, write, open, close, stat, fstat, lstat, poll, lseek
.TP
.B 16-23
ioctl, pread64, pwrite64, readv, writev, access, pipe, select
.TP
.B 32-33, 40, 72, 74-77
dup, dup2, sendfile, fcntl, fsync, fdatasync, truncate, ftruncate
.TP
.B 79-95
getcwd, chdir, rename, mkdir, rmdir, creat, link, unlink, symlink, readlink,
chmod, fchmod, chown, fchown, lchown, umask
.TP
.B 132, 162, 217, 235
utime, sync, getdents64, utimes
.TP
.B 257-270
openat, mkdirat, mknodat, fchownat, futimesat, newfstatat, unlinkat, renameat,
linkat, symlinkat, readlinkat, fchmodat, faccessat, pselect6
.TP
.B 280, 292-293
utimensat, dup3, pipe2
.TP
.B 316, 332, 439
renameat2 (zero flags only), statx (partial), faccessat2
.SS Processes, signals, identity, and time
.TP
.B 13-15
rt_sigaction, rt_sigprocmask, rt_sigreturn
.TP
.B 35-39
nanosleep, getitimer, alarm, setitimer, getpid
.TP
.B 56-63
clone, fork, vfork, execve, exit, wait4, kill, uname
.TP
.B 97, 102-123
getrlimit, getuid, getgid, setuid, setgid, geteuid, getegid, setpgid, getppid,
getpgrp, setsid, setreuid, setregid, getgroups, setgroups, setresuid, getresuid,
setresgid, getresgid, getpgid, setfsuid, setfsgid
.TP
.B 127, 131, 157-158, 169-170
rt_sigpending, sigaltstack, prctl, arch_prctl, reboot, sethostname
.TP
.B 186, 202, 218
gettid (same value as getpid), futex (basic wait and wake operations),
set_tid_address
.TP
.B 228-229, 231
clock_gettime, clock_getres, exit_group
.TP
.B 273, 302, 318
set_robust_list (metadata only), prlimit64 (limited), getrandom
(non-cryptographic generator)
.SS Memory
.TP
.B 9-12
mmap (anonymous and limited file-backed mappings), mprotect (coarse
present/write protection), munmap, brk
.TP
.B 28
madvise (compatibility no-op)
.SS Sockets
.TP
.B 41-55
socket, connect, accept, sendto, recvfrom, sendmsg, recvmsg, shutdown, bind,
listen, getsockname, getpeername, socketpair, setsockopt, getsockopt
.TP
.B 288
accept4
.PP
Socket support is limited to pathname AF_UNIX stream sockets and a small
AF_INET stack providing ARP, DHCP, ICMP, UDP, and client-side TCP.  Socket
options are mostly compatibility behavior rather than Linux-equivalent tuning.
.PP
Filesystem mutation works only on writable ext2/ext3 or RAM-backed mounts.
The root initramfs and shipped /usr filesystem are read-only.  VibeOS has no
real /proc or /sys filesystem, no separate thread IDs, and no full Linux clone,
futex, signal, virtual-memory, or networking contract.
.PP
Syscall 334 (rseq) is deliberately rejected with
.BR ENOSYS .
